results.title: Avengers (1963) #211
results.description: When Captain America holds an open call for Avengers applicants, the mansion is swarmed by X-Men, former members, anti-heroes, and a cat-woman named Tigra. Tigra’s introductory issue as member of the Avengers!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #212
results.description: A lover’s quarrel between two immortal beings threatens the entirety of D.C. Meet Linnea, the Elf queen in exile, who dukes it out with her warrior mate, Gorn. Gorn, humiliated by Linnea’s expansive power, strikes her.  Why are the Avengers involved? Good question!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #213
results.description: Yellowjacket continues to cause concern for his teammates after several bouts of reckless behavior in battle. But who will truly take the blunt of Hank Pym’s rage? Will it be the woman he loves more than life itself? A shocking issue that reveals the dark side to one of Earth’s Mightiest Heroes!

results.title: Court-Martial
results.description: Yellowjacket suspended from the Avengers; no real villain

results.title: Avengers (1963) #214
results.description: The Avengers head to the deserts of New Mexico to investigate an unprovoked attack on Warren Worthington, and his girlfriend Candy Southern. Yellowjacket attempts to reconcile with Jan, but she has already motioned for divorce. Guest-starring Ghost Rider!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #215
results.description: A special Silver Surfer-centric issue! What happens when Silver Surfer discovers the discarded wand of Molecule Man? And why is Tigra in grave danger because of this discovery?

results.title: Avengers (1963) #216
results.description: Secret identities are revealed when the Avengers are under the mercy of Molecule Man! The Silver Surfer must stand alone to save Earth’s Mightiest Heroes!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #217
results.description: Janet Van Dyne makes her triumphant return to the Avengers, and requests a position of leadership. Meanwhile, a disgraced Hank Pym agrees to create tech for an old arch nemesis. Enter Egghead, a dangerous criminal with mind-control powers!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #218
results.description: The Avengers grant a young boy access to the mansion, assuming that he is an innocent fan. But when the boy commits suicide in front of the team, only to have his body disintegrate and re-form, the Avengers realize they have entered the realm of the supernatural!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #219
results.description: Moondragon summons the remaining four Avengers after getting into trouble with a galactic warlord. Now, the Avengers find themselves in deep space, and deep trouble, with the inhabitants of the planet Ba-Bani!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #220
results.description: Moondragon continues to manipulate ally and foe alike with her telepathic powers. But has Drax the Destroyer had enough of her mind games? Plus, Moondragon faces the judgment of Odin after her enchantment spell on Thor goes awry!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #221
results.description: With only four full-time members, the Avengers must fill up their team roster! Will Spider-Man finally accept his bid as one of Earth’s Mightiest Heroes? Will Hawkeye be able to bury past grudges and rejoin the ranks? A new team of Avengers will be formed by the end of this issue!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #222
results.description: Egghead attempts to re-form the Masters of Evil, and his plans might just work! Hawkeye and She-Hulk continue their friendly feuding, while Jan finds herself “reacquainted” with an old flame.

results.title: Avengers (1963) #223
results.description: Hawkeye must face his past after an old circus colleague is threatened by Taskmaster. Featuring Scott Lang as Ant-Man!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #224
results.description: Scott Lang visits an incarcerated Hank Pym in an attempt to bolster his spirits. At a high society party, Jan finds herself rekindling an attraction to Tony Stark. But before romance can blossom between Tony and Jan, a revelation about the true identity of Iron Man must be revealed!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #225
results.description: The return of the Black Knight! After the team is transported to 12th century Avalon, the Avengers find themselves face-to-face with the monstrous Fomor! Who will perish in this alternate realm? And will it be the forces of good, or evil, that conquer the day?

results.title: Avengers (1963) #226
results.description: Will the Avengers remain trapped in the past? Will Avalon fall under the might of Balor? All will be revealed, including the fate of Black Knight, in this inter-dimensional issue!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #227
results.description: The Avengers test the capabilities of a new heroine calling herself Captain Marvel, and then offer her team membership. The Wasp continues to put up a brave front, determined to survive the turmoil of her divorce and to succeed as team chairwoman. Enter Monica Rambeau, as the new Captain Marvel!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #228
results.description: The Avengers, and the general public, anxiously await Hank Pym’s trial. But with Egghead alive and vengeful, the Masters of Evil may interrupt the due process of law!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #229
results.description: Tony Stark creates a cerebral scanner that will determine Hank Pym’s innocence. Jennifer Walters reverts back to She-Hulk after a heated argument with Hawkeye. Plus, the Avengers witness Hank Pym’s single-handed victory over the Masters of Evil!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #230
results.description: After Hank Pym is exonerated of all crimes, he leaves the Avengers for a new civilian life. The Masters of Evil are finally behind bars, and the team can breathe a collective sigh of relief. A new dawn awaits the Avengers!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #231
results.description: After the devastating battle against the Ultron, the Avengers’ tend to their wounds and bury their fallen comrades. But things seem to keep getting worse as they receive a phone call from a long-absent Iron Man. Read and find out what Tony Stark has to say! Plus: Eros comes to Earth!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #232
results.description: Captain Marvel and Starfox join the Avengers as full-fledged members! Their first mission: Take down the villain known as Plantman! Plus: Tony Stark, the former Ironed Avenger, succumbs to alcoholism!

results.title: And Now ... Starfox!
results.description: Eros becomes Starfox and joins Avengers; GA: Iron Man II (Rhodey Rhodes); V: Plant-Man, Wizard

results.title: Avengers (1963) #233
results.description: Annihilus has escaped and has taken the Fantastic Four captive! But before Earth’s Mightiest Heroes can rescue them, they must first get through the barrier! Will our heroes prove victorious before Annihilus has his way?

items.name: Fantastic Four Visionaries: John Byrne Vol. 3 (2004)
Fantastic Four Visionaries: John Byrne Vol. 3 (Trade Paperback)

results.title: Avengers (1963) #234
results.description: It’s the season of the witch… the Scarlet Witch that is. When a distraught Wanda takes over the Avengers Mansion, it’s up to her fellow teammates and friends to calm the mad witch down. Take a look into the mind of a true witch!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #235
results.description: The Wizard has escaped from prison! Who will survive his Mansion of Mechanized Mayhem!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #236
results.description: Spider-Man is back! Seeking an above minimum wage job, New York’s friendly neighborhood spider joins the Earth’s Mightiest Heroes! Plus: Blackout, unleashed!

results.title: I Want To Be An Avenger
Avengers (1963) #237
results.description: It’s the Avengers versus Electro, Blackout, Moonstone, and Rhino! Read to witness the explosive conclusion! Plus: Find out why Spider-Man must decline his invitation to join the Avengers, Earth’s Mightiest Heroes!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #238
results.description: The Vision speaks! With the help of Starfox’s home technology, the Avengers aid their robotic teammate in recovering from his epic battle against Annihilus! Meanwhile, Moonstone grows stronger, using her telepathic abilities to turn Blackout into her mind puppet.

results.title: Avengers (1963) #239
results.description: You’re not going to want to miss this hilarious issue!  It’s the Avengers on Late Night with David Letterman!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #240
results.description: Spider-Woman is trapped on the Astral Plane! When the missing Spider-Woman’s body is found, Dr. Strange and Hank Pym rush to revive her body. With Spider-Woman’s astral self transfixed between dimensions, is there any hope for her survival?

results.title: Avengers (1963) #241
results.description: It’s the mighty Avengers versus the magical menace of Morgan Le Fey! With the Mad Witch after the comatose body of Jessica Drew, the Avengers must spring into action to stop her before her plans are complete!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #242
results.description: Times are looking bright for our heroes as both old and new members return to the place where all began, the Avengers Mansion. But when the Vision detects a near infinite power approaching the Avengers must rally their troops, for darkness is coming!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #243
results.description: With all of his teammates missing in action, the Vision, acting as the Avengers’ Chairman must try to quell public panic. But when the absence of his teammates looks to be permanent the Vision declares a new team of Avengers must rise! Enter: The West Coast Avengers!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #244
results.description: Responding to suspected extraterrestrial sabotage at the Kennedy Space Center, the Avengers are on hand to stop a group of terrorists called the Rocketeers! Can the Avengers get to the bottom of this space mystery?

results.title: Avengers (1963) #245
results.description: It’s an all-out battle for the Avengers as they race against the clock to stop the aliens from carrying out their mission. Wasp and Captain Marvel must figure out of way of getting the space ship to return safely into the Earth’s atmosphere. Will they succeed? Or will the crashing space-craft cause mass destruction?

results.title: Avengers (1963) #246
results.description: With the threat from outer space taken care of, Earth’s Mightiest Heroes get back to rebuilding the team’s assets. First on the list: a new place to call HQ!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #247
results.description: In this issue: The Eternals reveal their origin and the truth about Starfox and his fellow Titanians comes to light! Plus: The missing Avengers--found!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #248
results.description: When Maelstrom targets the Uni-Mind in an evil plot to kill the Eternals, The Avengers spring into action to save them. Will the Avengers’ combined might be enough to stop Maelstrom and his ally, Deathurge? Find out in this action-packed issue!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #249
results.description: The Casket of Ancient Winters, an Asgardian power object, has unleashed blizzards everywhere on Earth! Now, the Avengers must band together with rest of Earth’s heroes to battle the fire-demon Surtur and his hordes!

results.title: Avengers (1963) #250
results.description: Maelstrom is back from the dead! And he’s brought company; Helio, Phobius, and Gronk! Together the team of villains plot to gain absolute power by siphoning the energy of the Earth’s rotation! The Avengers won’t know what hit them!
